id: pm-4k6b
title: "Adaptive context relevance engine: multi-signal scoring over metadata, graph, and history drives context/next assembly under an explicit token budget"
description: "SDK-first adaptive ranking engine for pm context/next: derive multi-signal relevance from tracker metadata, graph, history, semantic search, and agent state, then assemble bounded-token context with explainable scores."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[3]: context,relevance,scale
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:18:52.486Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T15:12:12.161Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 960
acceptance_criteria: SDK exposes a documented pluggable context-scoring interface with the built-in multi-signal scorer as default; pm context/pm next accept a token-budget bound and pack results by score with graceful projection degradation; json output can include a per-signal score breakdown; ranking is deterministic for a fixed workspace state; hot path stays index-backed (no full scan) and meets pm-9rxu latency targets on the 100k and 1M benchmark workspaces; on small workspaces default ordering remains stable (golden tests); extension can replace the scorer end-to-end (exemplar test)
parent: pm-9rxu
risk: medium
confidence: medium
